[2026-03-06T20:50:38Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019rqyE9CpAg47vhBSDJmm22","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche Docker Base Image Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The default Dockerfile generated by `cloche init` builds `cloche-agent` from the cloche\n     9→Go source inside the image. This only works for the cloche project itself (which has the\n    10→source available). For any other project, the template is broken out of the box.\n    11→\n    12→The root `Dockerfile` (used by the cloche project's own `.cloche/`) makes the same\n    13→mistake, and is also unnecessarily large (based on `golang:1.25` for the final stage).\n    14→\n    15→## Solution\n    16→\n    17→A `cloche-base` image: a minimal Debian-slim image with `git` and `cloche-agent`\n    18→pre-installed. Projects start from this image and add their own tooling on top.\n    19→\n    20→Using `cloche-base` is **not required** — projects may use any Dockerfile they like.\n    21→\n    22→---\n    23→\n    24→## `cloche-base` image contents\n    25→\n    26→Built from `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` in the cloche repo.\n    27→\n    28→| Component | Why |\n    29→|-----------|-----|\n    30→| `debian:12-slim` | Small, stable, widely compatible |\n    31→| `git` | Required by `cloche-agent` for branch/commit operations |\n    32→| `ca-certificates` | TLS for any outbound requests agents make |\n    33→| `cloche-agent` binary | The in-container workflow executor |\n    34→| `agent` user | Unprivileged user; workdir `/workspace` owned by `agent` |\n    35→\n    36→**Not included:** Node.js, npm, claude-code, language runtimes, build tools. These are\n    37→project-specific and belong in the project's own Dockerfile.\n    38→\n    39→### `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile`\n    40→\n    41→```dockerfile\n    42→FROM golang:1.25 AS builder\n    43→WORKDIR /src\n    44→COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n    45→RUN go mod download\n    46→COPY . .\n    47→RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o /cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n    48→\n    49→FROM debian:12-slim\n    50→RUN apt-get update \\\n    51→    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends git ca-certificates \\\n    52→    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    53→COPY --from=builder /cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\n    54→RUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\n    55→WORKDIR /workspace\n    56→RUN chown agent:agent /workspace\n    57→USER agent\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→Self-contained multi-stage build. No pre-built binary required on the host.\n    61→\n    62→---\n    63→\n    64→## Tags\n    65→\n    66→Both tags are applied on every build:\n    67→\n    68→- `cloche-base:latest`\n    69→- `cloche-base:<version>` — derived from `git describe --tags --always`\n    70→\n    71→Local only for now; registry publishing deferred.\n    72→\n    73→---\n    74→\n    75→## Makefile changes\n    76→\n    77→```makefile\n    78→VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n    79→\n    80→docker-base:\n    81→\tdocker build -f docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile \\\n    82→\t\t-t cloche-base:latest \\\n    83→\t\t-t cloche-base:$(VERSION) \\\n    84→\t\t.\n    85→\n    86→docker-build: docker-base\n    87→\tdocker build -t cloche-agent:latest -f .cloche/Dockerfile .\n    88→\n    89→install: build docker-build\n    90→\t...  (unchanged beyond this)\n    91→```\n    92→\n    93→`docker-build` now depends on `docker-base` so the cloche project image is always built\n    94→on top of a fresh base.\n    95→\n    96→---\n    97→\n    98→## Root `Dockerfile` update (cloche project's own image)\n    99→\n   100→The root `Dockerfile` (`.cloche/Dockerfile` for the cloche project) is simplified to\n   101→build on top of `cloche-base:latest`:\n   102→\n   103→```dockerfile\n   104→FROM cloche-base:latest\n   105→USER root\n   106→RUN apt-get update \\\n   107→    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs npm \\\n   108→    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   109→RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n   110→USER agent\n   111→```\n   112→\n   113→The golang builder stage is removed — `cloche-agent` now comes from the base.\n   114→\n   115→---\n   116→\n   117→## Default Dockerfile template (from `cloche init`)\n   118→\n   119→The template in `cmd/cloche/init.go` is replaced with:\n   120→\n   121→```dockerfile\n   122→FROM cloche-base:latest\n   123→USER root\n   124→\n   125→# Add your project's dependencies here.\n   126→# Example:\n   127→#   RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   128→#   RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n   129→\n   130→USER agent\n   131→```\n   132→\n   133→The `--image` flag to `cloche init` is repurposed as `--base-image` (default:\n   134→`cloche-base:latest`) to allow pinning to a specific version:\n   135→\n   136→```\n   137→cloche init --base-image cloche-base:v1.2.0\n   138→```\n   139→\n   140→This replaces the `FROM cloche-base:latest` line in the generated Dockerfile.\n   141→\n   142→---\n   143→\n   144→## Changes required\n   145→\n   146→| File | Change |\n   147→|------|--------|\n   148→| `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` | New file — base image definition |\n   149→| `Makefile` | Add `docker-base` target; make `docker-build` depend on it; add `VERSION` |\n   150→| `Dockerfile` (root / cloche project) | Simplify to `FROM cloche-base:latest` + add claude-code |\n   151→| `.cloche/Dockerfile` (cloche project) | Same simplification as root Dockerfile |\n   152→| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | New template using `cloche-base:latest`; rename `--image` to `--base-image` |\n   153→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58dedd6a-5fa6-4c74-93ac-0db4766733d4","uuid":"e751e8a6-6846-43f8-86bc-8e1aaef71fae","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md","content":"# Cloche Docker Base Image Design\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nThe default Dockerfile generated by `cloche init` builds `cloche-agent` from the cloche\nGo source inside the image. This only works for the cloche project itself (which has the\nsource available). For any other project, the template is broken out of the box.\n\nThe root `Dockerfile` (used by the cloche project's own `.cloche/`) makes the same\nmistake, and is also unnecessarily large (based on `golang:1.25` for the final stage).\n\n## Solution\n\nA `cloche-base` image: a minimal Debian-slim image with `git` and `cloche-agent`\npre-installed. Projects start from this image and add their own tooling on top.\n\nUsing `cloche-base` is **not required** — projects may use any Dockerfile they like.\n\n---\n\n## `cloche-base` image contents\n\nBuilt from `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` in the cloche repo.\n\n| Component | Why |\n|-----------|-----|\n| `debian:12-slim` | Small, stable, widely compatible |\n| `git` | Required by `cloche-agent` for branch/commit operations |\n| `ca-certificates` | TLS for any outbound requests agents make |\n| `cloche-agent` binary | The in-container workflow executor |\n| `agent` user | Unprivileged user; workdir `/workspace` owned by `agent` |\n\n**Not included:** Node.js, npm, claude-code, language runtimes, build tools. These are\nproject-specific and belong in the project's own Dockerfile.\n\n### `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile`\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM golang:1.25 AS builder\nWORKDIR /src\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY . .\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o /cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n\nFROM debian:12-slim\nRUN apt-get update \\\n    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends git ca-certificates \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\nCOPY --from=builder /cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\nRUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\nWORKDIR /workspace\nRUN chown agent:agent /workspace\nUSER agent\n```\n\nSelf-contained multi-stage build. No pre-built binary required on the host.\n\n---\n\n## Tags\n\nBoth tags are applied on every build:\n\n- `cloche-base:latest`\n- `cloche-base:<version>` — derived from `git describe --tags --always`\n\nLocal only for now; registry publishing deferred.\n\n---\n\n## Makefile changes\n\n```makefile\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n\ndocker-base:\n\tdocker build -f docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile \\\n\t\t-t cloche-base:latest \\\n\t\t-t cloche-base:$(VERSION) \\\n\t\t.\n\ndocker-build: docker-base\n\tdocker build -t cloche-agent:latest -f .cloche/Dockerfile .\n\ninstall: build docker-build\n\t...  (unchanged beyond this)\n```\n\n`docker-build` now depends on `docker-base` so the cloche project image is always built\non top of a fresh base.\n\n---\n\n## Root `Dockerfile` update (cloche project's own image)\n\nThe root `Dockerfile` (`.cloche/Dockerfile` for the cloche project) is simplified to\nbuild on top of `cloche-base:latest`:\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update \\\n    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs npm \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\nRUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\nUSER agent\n```\n\nThe golang builder stage is removed — `cloche-agent` now comes from the base.\n\n---\n\n## Default Dockerfile template (from `cloche init`)\n\nThe template in `cmd/cloche/init.go` is replaced with:\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\n\n# Add your project's dependencies here.\n# Example:\n#   RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n#   RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n\nUSER agent\n```\n\nThe `--image` flag to `cloche init` is repurposed as `--base-image` (default:\n`cloche-base:latest`) to allow pinning to a specific version:\n\n```\ncloche init --base-image cloche-base:v1.2.0\n```\n\nThis replaces the `FROM cloche-base:latest` line in the generated Dockerfile.\n\n---\n\n## Changes required\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` | New file — base image definition |\n| `Makefile` | Add `docker-base` target; make `docker-build` depend on it; add `VERSION` |\n| `Dockerfile` (root / cloche project) | Simplify to `FROM cloche-base:latest` + add claude-code |\n| `.cloche/Dockerfile` (cloche project) | Same simplification as root Dockerfile |\n| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | New template using `cloche-base:latest`; rename `--image` to `--base-image` |\n","numLines":153,"startLine":1,"totalLines":153}}}
[2026-03-06T20:50:38Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Af6bcnaavTnfv3d9BJwrHb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→.PHONY: build test lint clean proto docker-build install\n     2→\n     3→PREFIX ?= $(HOME)/.local\n     4→\n     5→build:\n     6→\tgo build -o bin/cloche ./cmd/cloche\n     7→\tgo build -o bin/cloched ./cmd/cloched\n     8→\tgo build -o bin/cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n     9→\n    10→test:\n    11→\tgo test ./... -v\n    12→\n    13→test-short:\n    14→\tgo test ./... -short\n    15→\n    16→lint:\n    17→\tgo vet ./...\n    18→\n    19→proto:\n    20→\tmkdir -p api/clochepb\n    21→\tprotoc --proto_path=api/proto/cloche/v1 \\\n    22→\t\t--go_out=api/clochepb --go_opt=paths=source_relative \\\n    23→\t\t--go-grpc_out=api/clochepb --go-grpc_opt=paths=source_relative \\\n    24→\t\tapi/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto\n    25→\n    26→docker-build:\n    27→\tdocker build -t cloche-agent:latest .\n    28→\n    29→install: build docker-build\n    30→\t@# Stop running daemon (graceful via CLI, fallback to kill)\n    31→\t@echo \"==> Stopping cloched...\"\n    32→\t@cloche shutdown 2>/dev/null || pkill -x cloched 2>/dev/null || true\n    33→\t@sleep 1\n    34→\t@# Install binaries\n    35→\t@mkdir -p $(PREFIX)/bin\n    36→\t@echo \"==> Installing to $(PREFIX)/bin/\"\n    37→\t@install bin/cloche bin/cloched bin/cloche-agent $(PREFIX)/bin/\n    38→\t@# Restart daemon\n    39→\t@echo \"==> Starting cloched...\"\n    40→\t@nohup $(PREFIX)/bin/cloched > /tmp/cloched.log 2>&1 &\n    41→\t@sleep 1\n    42→\t@pgrep -x cloched > /dev/null && echo \"==> cloched running (pid $$(pgrep -x cloched))\" || (echo \"==> ERROR: cloched failed to start, check /tmp/cloched.log\" && exit 1)\n    43→\t@echo \"==> Done\"\n    44→\n    45→clean:\n    46→\trm -rf bin/\n    47→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58dedd6a-5fa6-4c74-93ac-0db4766733d4","uuid":"938e7cea-1af4-4770-98b9-a4a396d657de","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/Makefile","content":".PHONY: build test lint clean proto docker-build install\n\nPREFIX ?= $(HOME)/.local\n\nbuild:\n\tgo build -o bin/cloche ./cmd/cloche\n\tgo build -o bin/cloched ./cmd/cloched\n\tgo build -o bin/cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n\ntest:\n\tgo test ./... -v\n\ntest-short:\n\tgo test ./... -short\n\nlint:\n\tgo vet ./...\n\nproto:\n\tmkdir -p api/clochepb\n\tprotoc --proto_path=api/proto/cloche/v1 \\\n\t\t--go_out=api/clochepb --go_opt=paths=source_relative \\\n\t\t--go-grpc_out=api/clochepb --go-grpc_opt=paths=source_relative \\\n\t\tapi/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto\n\ndocker-build:\n\tdocker build -t cloche-agent:latest .\n\ninstall: build docker-build\n\t@# Stop running daemon (graceful via CLI, fallback to kill)\n\t@echo \"==> Stopping cloched...\"\n\t@cloche shutdown 2>/dev/null || pkill -x cloched 2>/dev/null || true\n\t@sleep 1\n\t@# Install binaries\n\t@mkdir -p $(PREFIX)/bin\n\t@echo \"==> Installing to $(PREFIX)/bin/\"\n\t@install bin/cloche bin/cloched bin/cloche-agent $(PREFIX)/bin/\n\t@# Restart daemon\n\t@echo \"==> Starting cloched...\"\n\t@nohup $(PREFIX)/bin/cloched > /tmp/cloched.log 2>&1 &\n\t@sleep 1\n\t@pgrep -x cloched > /dev/null && echo \"==> cloched running (pid $$(pgrep -x cloched))\" || (echo \"==> ERROR: cloched failed to start, check /tmp/cloched.log\" && exit 1)\n\t@echo \"==> Done\"\n\nclean:\n\trm -rf bin/\n","numLines":47,"startLine":1,"totalLines":47}}}
